<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="790" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[168,775,831,1023]" pageId="17" pageNumber="790">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,279,831,855]" pageId="17" pageNumber="790">Remarks.</emphasis>
The collected specimen is a pre-adult individual. Ventral coloration is unusually pale gray, but the pholidosis corresponds to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1875" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Bothrocophias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="790" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microphthalmus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="790">Bothrocophias microphthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We prefer to be cautious and leave the identification as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[199,440,966,990]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Bothrocophias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="790" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microphthalmus">
<emphasis box="[199,222,966,989]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="790">B.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[265,440,966,990]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="790">microphthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until more specimens become available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
